  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of making illegally-obtained money appear legal by passing it through complex financial transactions. Key legal elements typically include:\n\n1. Concealing the source of illegally obtained funds\n2. Transforming monetary proceeds from criminal activities\n3. Attempting to make illegal funds look like legitimate income\n4. Engaging in financial transactions designed to hide the origin of money\n\nThe specific legal definition can vary between jurisdictions, but most definitions involve intentional efforts to disguise the proceeds of criminal activity.",
